    <item>
      <title>&#34;include:&#34; statement in Ansible  does not find the correct path running on Vagrant</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/include-statement-in-ansible--does-not-find-the-correct-path-running-on-vagrant/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Apr 2016 14:02:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/include-statement-in-ansible--does-not-find-the-correct-path-running-on-vagrant/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;What is the issue?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You have an include statement inside a role but when the playbook is running on Vagrant, that path doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist!!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tree:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;├── playbook.yml&#xA;└── roles&#xA;    ├── base&#xA;    │   ├── README.md&#xA;    │   ├── defaults&#xA;    │   │   └── main.yml&#xA;    │   ├── files&#xA;    │   ├── handlers&#xA;    │   │   └── main.yml&#xA;    │   ├── meta&#xA;    │   │   └── main.yml&#xA;    │   ├── tasks&#xA;    │   │   ├── main.yml&#xA;    │   │   ├── setup_debian.yml&#xA;    │   │   └── setup_rhel.yml&#xA;    │   ├── templates&#xA;    │   └── vars&#xA;    │       └── main.yml&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;In &lt;code&gt;tasks/main.yml&lt;/code&gt; we have:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
